; TickMessageQueue
;
; Per-frame driver of the message line's teletype effect. A message's
; life: dequeue -> RenderMessage draws it over black attributes ->
; a bright-red cursor sweeps left-to-right, turning each column
; black-on-cyan (the reveal) -> the message holds (timer 50, or just
; 2 when more messages wait) -> the cursor sweeps back right-to-left
; blacking it out -> the next message is fetched. MsgDrawnCol encodes
; the phase: 0 = line free, bit 7 set = revealing, bit 7 clear =
; erasing. Called twice per frame, so the sweeps run at ~100 cells/s.
; .
; Used by the routine at #R36457.
@nowarn=33709
