; Blits the alien tail (Y channel) XOR sprite for the current phase and position.
; First XORs ink colour bits of a 4x2 attribute block to produce a flash effect.
; Then loads the current Y-phase sprite pointer (3 bytes/row, 21 rows) and chooses
; between an unshifted XOR blit (JonesPos&7 < 4) or a shifted one (>= 4). The
; shift amount is encoded directly into the self-modifying JR at BlitJonesShiftCode
; (the JR offset byte is patched to select how many SRL/RR passes execute). DJNZ at the end
; re-uses B to call AdvanceJonesPos when B=2.
