; GameModeDispatchTable
@ignoreua
;
; 3-word jump table indexed by the highlighted game mode (0-2).
; JP (HL) at #R43134 lands here; the word for the current selection
; is loaded into HL and jumped to.
; .
;   Mode 0 — Short Game   → #R44738 (ShortGameInit)
;   Mode 1 — Long Game    → #R42276 (LongGameInit)
;   Mode 2 — Introduction → #R43242 (IntroductionMode)
; .
; Short vs Long Game summary (see the two init routines for full detail):
; .
;   AlienTargetID (#R33703):
;     - Short Game = 9, hard-wired at #R44751. Crucially, this is >= 8,
;       which the alien-event guard at #R41274 (TriggerAlienEvent's "CP 8
;       / RET NC") treats as "no valid target" — so the alien's targeted-
;       stalk logic is effectively disabled in Short Game and the alien
;       just roams.
;     - Long Game  = random pick from #R41390 (LongGameTargetTable, values
;                    in {1, 2, 4, 6}) at #R42357. Always < 8, so the alien
;                    actively hunts the chosen crew member.
; .
;   Chestburster host slot (HostMarker = byte+1=$FF, byte+7=$FF):
;     - Long Game  = exactly ONE slot, picked randomly via
;                    #R41374 (LongGameHostSlotTable, values {1,2,5}).
;                    That crew is the chestburster host — message #33
;                    enqueued at startup ("Alien has hatched from
;                    {actor}") substitutes this crew's name in.
;     - Short Game = FOUR pre-stamped slots in the template: Dallas (1),
;                    Kane (2), Ash (4) and Brett (7) are out of play,
;                    leaving only Ripley, Lambert and Parker — the
;                    film's final act — and no host subplot.
; .
; (The in-game "Android" of message #32 "{actor} hits the Android" is
; the crew slot selected into AlienTargetID #R33703 — see the notes at
; #R41390 and the activation logic in #R40826.)
; .
;   Starting crew/alien record state at $737E:
;     - Short Game = #R41508 (ShortGameCrewInit) — four slots pre-stamped
;                    with the HostMarker, yielding a smaller "active"
;                    starting cast
;     - Long Game  = #R41444 (LongGameCrewInit) — every slot starts with
;                    normal (non-$FF) data; LongGameInit then picks ONE
;                    slot via #R41374 (LongGameHostSlotTable, values
;                    in {1, 2, 5}) and stamps the HostMarker on that
;                    record's bytes +1 and +7
; .
;   Script-driven startup message:
;     - Short Game does not enqueue any startup message
;     - Long Game enqueues message #33 ("Alien has hatched from {actor}")
;       carrying the host slot index via #R37176 — the long game's
;       opening narrative beat naming the chestburster host
; .
; Both modes then fall through to #R42380 (CommonGameInit), which
; finishes the per-session setup identically (alien position, animation
; tables, room mode = 1 corridor view).
; .
; In short: the Short Game is a deterministic, abbreviated scenario; the
; Long Game uses the ROM-traversal script (#R33589) to randomise both
; the alien's first target and one tagged crew slot per run, producing a
; longer and more varied game.
@label=GameModeDispatchTable
w43135 DEFW 44738,42276,43242

; GameModeText
;
; $FF-terminated text strings for the game-mode menu, rendered by
; #R42821 (GameModeScreen) via five calls to #R31693.
; Indices 0-3 are the four menu lines; index 4 is the footer prompt.
@label=GameModeText
b43141 DEFB 49,58,32,83,104,111,114,116,32,71,97,109,101,255     ; "1: Short Game"
 43155 DEFB 50,58,32,76,111,110,103,32,71,97,109,101,255          ; "2: Long Game"
 43168 DEFB 51,58,32,73,110,116,114,111  ; "3: Intro
 43176 DEFB 100,117,99,116,105,111,110,255  ; duction"
 43184 DEFB 52,58,32,83,101,108,101,99,116,255                    ; "4: Select"
 43194 DEFB 80,114,101,115,115,32,65,112,112,114,111  ; "Press Appro
 43205 DEFB 112,114,105,97,116,101,32,75,101,121,255  ; priate Key"

; HighlightGameMode
@ignoreua
;
; XOR-toggles the attribute colour of the currently selected menu
; row, used by GameModeScreen (#R42821) to highlight or erase the
; cursor. Loads the base attribute address $59E9 (row 15, col 9),
; steps 64 bytes per row (selection × 64), then XORs 15 consecutive
; attribute bytes with 36 (flipping ink/paper to show highlight).
@label=HighlightGameMode
c43216 LD HL,23017   ;
; This entry point is used by the routine at #R43610.
@label=HighlightModeAt
*43219 LD DE,64      ;
@nowarn=33683
@ssub=LD A,(CorridorCursor)
 43222 LD A,(33683)  ;
 43225 AND A         ;
 43226 JR Z,43232    ;
