; CheckCrewAlive — the per-frame crew-extinction gate
;
; Formerly mislabelled "DrawStatusPanel" — it draws nothing. Called
; once per frame from the main loop: walk the +7 status column of crew
; slots 1-7 and return as soon as any HUMAN crew member is still alive
; (status 0). The Android slot (#R33703) is skipped — an Android alone
; does not keep the mission going. If no live human is found, fall
; through to Endgame_CrewLost (#R44242): "Humanoid life levels
; minimal". (Short Game: AlienTargetID is 9, so no slot is skipped;
; the four absent crew have non-zero status from ShortGameCrewInit.)
